input: Why do you think I can not apply a subscription code?
gold_answer: You might not be able to apply a subscription code because you don't have the required access in the account or the code expired. To successfully apply a subscription code, you must have an Editor role or higher on all account management services. If the expired code needs to be reissued, you would need to contact the person who provided the code for help with reissuing a new one.

retrieved_contexts.text:
Why can't I apply a subscription code? 

To successfully apply a subscription code, make sure the code is valid and you have the required access.

  What’s happening 

When you try to apply a subscription code, you see an error that states that the code cannot be applied.

  Why it’s happening 

You might see this error if you don't have the required access in the account or the code expired.

  How to fix it 

Use the following options:



*  Verify that you have access to apply the code. To apply any code, you must have an Editor role or higher on all account management services. To view or change roles, see [Assigning access to account management services](https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/account?topic=account-account-services).
*  Contact the person who provided the code for help with reissuing an expired code.
